Key Match Events: The Houston Rockets lost to the Oklahoma City Thunder, 126-107.
The Thunder shot 51.1% from the field and 37.8% from deep.
Post-Match Reflections: Panic has commenced among Rockets fans due to offensive struggles.
Houston's stars have been inconsistent from the field, with no starter shooting above 44% and three of five starters shooting under 30% from three.
Head coach Ime Udoka has struggled to will the team on the offensive end.
Alperen Sengun is averaging 15.8 points, 11.1 rebounds, 4.1 assists, 1.1 steals, and 1.1 blocks despite a decrease in minutes.
Houston fans are advised not to panic as the team is young and expected to improve as the season progresses.
